verses.text: Now the children of Reuben and the children of Gad had a very great multitude of cattle : and when they saw the land of Jazer , and the land of Gilead , that, behold, the place \add was\add* a place for cattle ;
The children of Gad and the children of Reuben came and spake unto Moses , and to Eleazar the priest , and unto the princes of the congregation , saying ,

Ataroth , and Dibon , and Jazer , and Nimrah , and Heshbon , and Elealeh , and Shebam , and Nebo , and Beon ,\f + \fr 32.3 \ft Nimrah: also called, Beth-nimrah\f*\f + \fr 32.3 \ft Shebam: also called, Shibmah\f*\f + \fr 32.3 \ft Beon: also called, Baal-meon\f*
\add Even\add* the country which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* smote before the congregation of Israel , \add is\add* a land for cattle , and thy servants have cattle :
Wherefore, said they, if we have found grace in thy sight , let this land be given unto thy servants for a possession , \add and\add* bring us not over Jordan. \p
¶ And Moses said unto the children of Gad and to the children of Reuben , Shall your brethren go to war , and shall ye sit here?
And wherefore discourage ye the heart of the children of Israel from going over into the land which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath given them?\f + \fr 32.7 \ft discourage: Heb. break\f*
Thus did your fathers , when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea to see the land.

For when they went up unto the valley of Eshcol , and saw the land , they discouraged the heart of the children of Israel , that they should not go into the land which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had given them.
And the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* anger was kindled the same time , and he sware , saying ,

Surely none of the men that came up out of Egypt , from twenty years old and upward , shall see the land which I sware unto Abraham , unto Isaac , and unto Jacob ; because they have not wholly followed me:\f + \fr 32.11 \ft wholly…: Heb. fulfilled after me\f*
Save Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenezite , and Joshua the son of Nun : for they have wholly followed the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And the 
d \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* anger was kindled against Israel , and he made them wander in the wilderness forty years , until all the generation , that had done evil in the sight of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, was consumed.
And, behold, ye are risen up in your fathers’ stead, an increase of sinful men , to augment yet the fierce anger of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* toward Israel.
For if ye turn away from after him, he will yet again leave them in the wilderness ; and ye shall destroy all this people. \p
¶ And they came near unto him, and said , We will build sheepfolds here for our cattle , and cities for our little ones :

But we ourselves will go ready armed before the children of Israel , until we have brought them unto their place : and our little ones shall dwell in the fenced cities because of the inhabitants of the land.
We will not return unto our houses , until the children of Israel have inherited every man his inheritance.
For we will not inherit with them on yonder side Jordan , or forward ; because our inheritance is fallen to us on this side Jordan eastward. \p
¶ And Moses said unto them, If ye will do this thing , if ye will go armed before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* to war ,
And will go all of you armed over Jordan before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, until he hath driven out his enemies from before him,

And the land be subdued before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: then afterward ye shall return , and be guiltless before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, and before Israel ; and this land shall be your possession before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.
But if ye will not do so , behold, ye have sinned against the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: and be sure your sin will find you out.
Build you cities for your little ones , and folds for your sheep ; and do that which hath proceeded out of your mouth.
And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben spake unto Moses , saying , Thy servants will do as my lord commandeth.
Our little ones , our wives , our flocks , and all our cattle , shall be there in the cities of Gilead :
But thy servants will pass over , every man armed for war , before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* to battle , as my lord saith. \p
So concerning them Moses commanded Eleazar the priest , and Joshua the son of Nun , and the chief fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel :

And Moses said unto them, If the children of Gad and the children of Reuben will pass with you over Jordan , every man armed to battle , before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and the land shall be subdued before you; then ye shall give them the land of Gilead for a possession :
But if they will not pass over with you armed , they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan.
And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered , saying , As the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath said unto thy servants , so will we do.
We will pass over armed before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* into the land of Canaan , that the possession of our inheritance on this side Jordan \add may be\add* ours.

And Moses gave unto them, \add even\add* to the children of Gad , and to the children of Reuben , and unto half the tribe of Manasseh the son of Joseph , the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites , and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan , the land , with the cities thereof in the coasts , \add even\add* the cities of the country round about. \p
¶ And the children of Gad built Dibon , and Ataroth , and Aroer ,
And Atroth, Shophan , and Jaazer , and Jogbehah ,\f + \fr 32.35 \ft Jaazer: also called, Jazer\f*
And Beth-nimrah , and Beth-haran , fenced cities : and folds for sheep.\f + \fr 32.36 \ft Beth-nimrah: also called, Nimrah\f*
And the children of Reuben built Heshbon , and Elealeh , and Kirjathaim ,

And Nebo , and Baal-meon , (their names being changed ,) and Shibmah : and gave other names unto the cities which they builded.\f + \fr 32.38 \ft gave…: Heb. they called by names the names of the cities\f*
And the children of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead , and took it, and dispossessed the Amorite which \add was\add* in it.
And Moses gave Gilead unto Machir the son of Manasseh ; and he dwelt therein.
And Jair the son of Manasseh went and took the small towns thereof, and called them Havoth-jair.
And Nobah went and took Kenath , and the villages thereof, and called it Nobah , after his own name.
